### To login to AWS instance 
ssh -i "ssh key file" ec2-user@ec2-3-138-118-214.us-east-2.compute.amazonaws.com
ssh -i (pathtosshjkeyfile) ec2-user@ 18.116.51.87(IP may change)

### To start instance
aws ec2 start-instances --instance-id (instanceid)

### To stop instance 
aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-id (instanceid)

### If login does not work 
change key permission to 400 using: chmod 400 (The key file)
Move the key to your home directory for easier access 

### To describe instance (This is a script.Run this from the local machine before logging into remote)
aws ec2 describe-instances --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].{PublicIP:PublicIpAddress,Name:Tags[?Key=='Name']|[0].Value,Status:State.Name,ElasticIPAddress:ElasticIpAddress,InstanceID:InstanceId,InstanceType:InstanceType,SubnetID:SubnetId,VPCID:VpcId}" --output table | grep -v terminated 

### To see layout of filesystem
df -hP

### configuring devbox
first install brew and update 
then run this: brew install terraform ansible git eksctl kubectl jq argocd

### To set up an alias 

### Creating s3 bucket
aws s3 mb s3://(bucket name)
aws s3 ls 

### To check aws integration(make sure it's working effectively)
aws s3 ls (should able to show created buckets or run without errror)

### To check aws config file 
~/.aws/config 

### How to check awscli version 
aws --version

###aws config file
~/.aws/config

### To check aws credentials file 
cat ~/.aws/credentials



